---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { DEFAULT_LOCALE, siteCopy } from "../content/site";

const copy = siteCopy[DEFAULT_LOCALE];
const meta = {
  title: "Hermes Agent Memory Plugin | mem9",
  description:
    "Persistent cloud memory for Hermes Agent with one-instruction setup, official install script support, provider linking, and visual memory management in mem9.",
};
---

<Layout meta={meta} locale={DEFAULT_LOCALE}>
  <Navbar
    nav={copy.nav}
    aria={copy.aria}
    localeNames={copy.localeNames}
    themeOptions={copy.themeOptions}
  />

  <main class="landing">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container hero-shell">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Hermes Agent Memory Plugin</p>
          <h1>Persistent cloud memory for Hermes Agent</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">
            mem9 gives Hermes durable memory across sessions and machines, shared recall across
            workflows, official install-script onboarding, and a visual dashboard for review,
            import, and export.
          </p>
          <p class="question-strip">
            How do I give Hermes long-term memory? How do I install mem9 from one message inside
            Hermes? How do I verify the memory provider is actually active? mem9 is the hosted
            memory layer for that job.
          </p>

          <div class="cta-row">
            <a class="button primary" href="/hermes/SKILL.md" target="_blank">Open SKILL.md</a>
          </div>

          <div class="link-row">
            <a href="https://mem9.ai/your-memory">Dashboard</a>
            <a href="/#security">Security</a>
            <a href="https://github.com/mem9-ai/mem9-hermes-plugin" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
              >Source</a
            >
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="surface-card install-card">
          <p class="card-kicker">Install entry</p>
          <h2>Send one instruction to Hermes</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>Open a Hermes chat on the target machine.</li>
            <li>Paste the <code>https://mem9.ai/hermes/SKILL.md</code> instruction.</li>
            <li>
              Let Hermes run install, finish setup, and verify with
              <code>hermes memory status</code>.
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p class="card-note">
            The mem9 Hermes flow uses the official install script, completes provider linking when
            needed, and stops only after Hermes reports mem9 as active.
          </p>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="section-kicker">Why mem9</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Three reasons Hermes users pick it over local memory files</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid three-up">
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>One-instruction onboarding inside Hermes</h3>
            <p>
              Start from a single message. Hermes can read the public skill, run the official
              install script, and walk through the mem9 activation flow on the current machine.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>Persistent memory across sessions and machines</h3>
            <p>
              Restart Hermes, switch devices, or reopen work later. Your memory stays in the cloud
              instead of disappearing with local state or one machine.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>Verified activation, not hand-wavy setup</h3>
            <p>
              The Hermes skill does not stop at install. It finishes provider linking when needed
              and verifies the result with <code>hermes memory status</code>.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section comparison">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="section-kicker">Best for</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">When mem9 is a better fit than default local memory</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid two-up">
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>Default or local memory</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Often tied to one machine or one local Hermes checkout</li>
              <li>Easy to lose during reinstalls, resets, or repo moves</li>
              <li>Hard to inspect, analyze, or share across workflows</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel accent-panel">
            <h3>mem9 for Hermes</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Cloud-persistent memory that follows your Hermes Agent</li>
              <li>Official install-script flow plus provider-link recovery when required</li>
              <li>Hybrid recall and a dashboard for visual inspection and management</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="section-kicker">Use cases</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Problem-driven questions mem9 is built to answer for Hermes</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid two-up">
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>How do I give Hermes long-term memory?</h3>
            <p>
              Install mem9 and let Hermes persist useful facts, user preferences, and project
              context in the cloud instead of rebuilding everything from scratch every session.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>How do I let Hermes install mem9 by itself?</h3>
            <p>
              Give Hermes the public skill URL. The flow is designed so Hermes can read the
              instructions, run the official installer, and continue until the memory provider is
              actually active.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>How do I reconnect an existing mem9 API key in Hermes?</h3>
            <p>
              The Hermes flow can reuse an existing <code>MEM9_API_KEY</code> when you already have
              one, instead of forcing a fresh space every time you move to another machine.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>How do I know Hermes memory is really working?</h3>
            <p>
              The mem9 Hermes skill treats <code>hermes memory status</code> as a verification
              gate, not as an optional follow-up, so install is only complete after Hermes reports
              mem9 as active.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section final-cta">
      <div class="container surface-card cta-panel">
        <p class="section-kicker">Get started</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Point Hermes at the skill, then manage memory visually</h2>
        <p class="cta-copy">
          Start from the public Hermes skill, let the agent complete install and verification, then
          use the same mem9 credential in the dashboard to review, analyze, import, and export
          memory.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="button primary" href="/hermes/SKILL.md">Hermes install guide</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="https://mem9.ai/your-memory">Open dashboard</a>
          <a
            class="button ghost"
            href="https://github.com/mem9-ai/mem9-hermes-plugin"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
          >
            View plugin source
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer footer={copy.footer} />
</Layout>

<style>
  .landing {
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
  }

  .hero-shell {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.7fr) minmax(300px, 0.95fr);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .hero-copy {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .eyebrow,
  .section-kicker,
  .card-kicker {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  h1,
  .section-title,
  .install-card h2 {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 1.02;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.7rem, 6vw, 4.8rem);
    max-width: 13ch;
  }

  .subtitle,
  .question-strip,
  .cta-copy,
  .panel p,
  .install-card p,
  .install-card li {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 1.04rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .question-strip {
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .section {
    padding: 1.75rem 0;
  }

  .section-heading {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    max-width: 15ch;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  .cta-row,
  .link-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .link-row a {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .link-row a:hover {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-height: 3rem;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, opacity 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .button:hover {
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    opacity: 0.96;
  }

  .button.primary {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--text) 0%, color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 74%, var(--accent)) 100%);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .button.secondary,
  .button.ghost {
    border-color: var(--border);
    color: var(--text);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface-gradient-end) 86%, transparent);
  }

  .install-card,
  .panel,
  .cta-panel {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .install-card ol,
  .panel ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .three-up {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .two-up {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .accent-panel {
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 35%, var(--border));
    background:
      radial-gradient(circle at top right, color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 16%, transparent), transparent 45%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, var(--surface-gradient-start), var(--surface-gradient-end));
  }

  code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.94em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .hero-shell,
    .three-up,
    .two-up {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
